              <h4>Invoices</h4>

              <p>
                Invoices are to be completed and submitted semi-monthly:
              <ul>
                <li>for the period from the 1st to the 15th of the month, and</li>
                <li>for the period from the 16th to the end of the month (EOM)</li>
              </ul>
              </p>

              <p>
                <i>
                  <b>Invoices are due by 5pm on the 16th and the 1st of each month every month, respectively.</b>
                  Invoices that are received after those dates may be delayed to the next invoice period so please make
                  sure that you get your invoices get in on time!</i>
              </p>

              <p>
                Here are some sample invoice templates that you can use or please feel free to use your own.
                <%= link_to 'Click here to view sample invoices.', 'https://templates.office.com/en-US/Invoices' %>
              </p>

              <p>
                Completed invoices should be submitted as a PDF file and should include all of the following:
              <p>
              <ul>
                <li>List of confirmed client interviews for the invoice period and the dates that those client
                  interviews took place
                </li>
                <li>List of submitted candidates for the invoice period and the dates that those candidates were
                  submitted
                </li>
                <li>List of hires for the invoice period and the date that each new hire started their new job</li>
                <li>Starting and ending dates of invoice period</li>
                <li>Hours worked per week during invoice period</li>
              </ul>
              </p>

              <h4>Submit invoices to:</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Invoices Team: invoices@cardinalhire.com</li>
                <li>Raj: rs.cardinalop@gmail.com</li>
                <li>PCC: paul@cardinalhire.com</li>
                <li>TL: teamleon@gmail.com</li>
              </ul>
              </p>

              <h4>Invoice Approvals</h4>
              <p>Invoices are subject to review and approval from CH Operations.</p>

              <h4>Invoice Payments</h4>

              <p>
                Payments can be via check or direct bank transfer.
              </p>

              <p>
                CH may choose to issue all SF Bay Area payments by CH check, for Contractors to pick up from CH Office.
                (CH may request SF Bay Area Contractors to attend meetings/etc at CH Office ... weekly/monthly/TBD).
              </p>

              <h4>Payment Processing</h4>
              <p>
                Invoices must be submitted to and approved by CH Operations before payment processing. CH Operations
                will process payments under timetable below (subject to change due to uncontrollable factors). CH
                Operations will process payments in weekly batches.
              </p>

              <h4>Payment Timetable</h4>
              <p>
                Present expectation .. payment processing/direct transfers (bank posting) 7 to 10 days after end of
                semimonthly period. Timetable subject to change, based on Bank's processing timetable. At present, Bank
                does not process on weekends or holidays, and
                Bank has 3 business day processing to non-BofA accounts.
              </p>

              <h4>Bank Processing Fees</h4>
              <p>
                For options other than checks which can be picked up at the CH office if that option is selected, CH
                will deduct Bank processing fees from Invoice amount/balance.
              </p>
              <p>
                Present Bank Fees ..
              <ul>
                <li>
                  CH checks .. no fee;
                </li>
                <li>
                  ACH to BofA account .. no fee;
                </li>
                <li>ACH to non-BofA account (3 business days processing time) .. $3 fee;</li>
                <li>ACH to non-BofA account (1 business day processing time) .. $10 fee;</li>
                <li>bank wire to ANY bank account (same business day) .. $30 fee;</li>
                <li>overseas bank wire (same business day) .. $35 to $45 fee;</li>
              </ul>
              </p>
